Burning,\" British Lion |url=https://eu.sctimes.com/story/entertainment/2020/01/22/local-cd-pick-the-burning-british-lion/4523344002/ |website=sctimes.com |accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Monkhouse |first1=Paul |title=Album Review : British Lion \u2013 \u2018The Burning |url=https://metalplanetmusic.com/2020/01/gig-review-british-lion-the-burning/ |website=Metal Planet Music |accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Popoff |first1=Martin |title=BRITISH LION \u2013 \u201cIT\u2019S EMOTIONAL AND IT\u2019S POWERFUL AND IT\u2019S REAL\u201d |url=http://bravewords.com/features/british-lion-its-emotional-and-its-powerful-and-its-real |website=BraveWords |accessdate=January 31, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Johnson |first1=Kevin |title=Steve Harris and British Lion Release \u201cThe Burning\u201d |url=https://www.notreble.com/buzz/2020/01/22/steve-harris-and-british-lion-release-the-burning/ |website=No Treble |accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref> It was released January 17, 2020, and was produced by Harris itself. It was the first album under only moniker British Lion, transforming the project from solo to band.\n\nThe album was preceded by the singles \"Spit Fire\" on October 26, 2018, \"Lightning\" on October 31, 2019, and the title track \"The Burning\" on December 13, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=IRON MAIDEN Bassist's BRITISH LION: Watch Music Video For 'The Burning' Title Track |url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/iron-maiden-bassists-british-lion-watch-music-video-for-the-burning-title-track/ |website=Blabbermouth.net |accessdate=January 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Kielty |first1=Martin |title=Listen to Steve Harris\u2019 New British Lion Song \u2018The Burning\u2019  Read More: Listen to Steve Harris\u2019 New British Lion Song \u2018The Burning\u2019 |url=https://ultimateclassicrock.com/british-lion-the-burning/ |website=ultimateclassicrock.com |accessdate=December 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Colothan |first1=Scott |title=Exclusive: British Lion premiere 'The Burning' video |url=https://planetradio.co.uk/planet-rock/news/rock-news/british-lion-the-burning-video/|website=planetradio.co.uk |accessdate=January 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Graff |first1=Gary |title=Steve Harris Shares Title Track to British Lion's 'The Burning': Premiere |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/8545910/british-lion-the-burning-steve-harris |website=Billboard |accessdate=November 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the release of '''''The Burning''''', critics published reviews on their thoughts of the album. '''Metal Planet Music''' voiced that \"the first thing that strikes you is the music, great hard rock with melody and class, but it\u2019s the heart and emotion that will stay with you long after the last note rings out. Coming eight years after their debut, \u2018'''''The Burning'''''\u2019 is the second album by '''British Lion''' and the [[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]] led quintet have made a record that is at once modern, nostalgic and timeless\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metalplanetmusic.com/2020/01/gig-review-british-lion-the-burning/|title=Album Review : British Lion \u2013 \u2018The Burning|last=Authoradmin|date=2020-01-22|website=Metal Planet Music|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n== Critical Reception ==\n[[Kerrang!]] mainly spoke upon the vocals of the album stating that \"the band\u2019s debut was rather a baptism of fire for singer '''Richard Taylor''', who had to weather some predictable yet redundant criticisms comparing him to [[Bruce Dickinson]] from Steve\u2019s \u201cother\u201d band. He sings like he has a point to prove throughout '''''The Burning'''''. A telling sign of the frontman\u2019s burgeoning confidence comes on '''Elysium''' \u2013 a song that boasts a killer chorus but an even better final passage, as he belts out a series of absolutely massive sustained notes over a swelling choral section. Equally impressive is his ability to extract emotion from a song. Whether he\u2019s communing with lost souls on '''Lightning''' or offering a consolatory ear on closer '''Native Son''', he often brings a moving sense of fragility to the fore. Clearly, this particular lion has more at its disposal than claws alone\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kerrang.com/reviews/album-review-british-lion-the-burning/|title=Album Review: British Lion \u2013 The Burning|website=Kerrang!|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n\n\n\n\n==Track listing==\nAll songs are written by Richard Taylor, David Hawkins and [[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]], except where noted.\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed       = \n| headline        =\n| total_length    = 60:11\n| title1          = City of Fallen Angels\n| length1         = 5:20\n| writer1         = \n\n| title2          = The Burning\n| length2         = 5:15\n| writer2         = \n\n| title3          = Father Lucifer\n| length3         = 4:38\n| writer3         = \n\n| title4          = Elysium\n| length4         = 5:11\n| writer4         =\n\n| title5          = Lightning\n| length5         = 5:49\n| writer5         = \n\n| title6          = Last Chance\n| length6         = 6:05\n| writer6         = Grahame Leslie, Ian Roberts, Taylor, Harris\n\n| title7          = Legend\n| length7         = 4:06\n| writer7         = \n\n| title8          = Spit Fire\n| length8         = 6:19\n| writer8         = \n\n| title9          = Land of the Perfect People\n| length9         = 4:52\n| writer9         = Taylor, Harris\n\n| title10         = Bible Black \n| length10        = 6:33\n| writer10        = \n\n| title11         = Native Son\n| length11        = 6:03\n| writer11        = \n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n*Richard Taylor - vocals\n*David Hawkins - guitars\n*Grahame Leslie - guitars\n*[[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]] - bass guitars, keyboards, production\n*Simon Dawson - drums\n\n===Additional personnel===\n*Tony Newton - engineering, recording, mixing\n*Ade Emsley - mastering\n*John McMurtrie - photography\n*Gustavo Sazes - album cover\n*Matt Cox - templating, booklet artwork \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Burning, The}}\n[[Category:Heavy metal albums by English artists]]\n[[Category:2020 albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = The Burning\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[British Lion (band)|British Lion]]\n| cover      = British Lion The Burning.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = January 17, 2020\n| recorded   = \n| venue      = \n| studio     = Barnyard Studio, Harlow, Essex, UK\n| genre      = [[Heavy metal music|Heavy metal]] \n| length     = 60:11\n| label      = *[[Parlophone]] <small>(International edition)</small>\n*Explorer1 Music, LLC\n*[[Warner Music]] <small>(Japanese edition)</small>\n| producer   = [[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]]\n| prev_title = [[British Lion (album)|British Lion]]\n| prev_year  = 2012\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = The Burning\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Spit Fire\n | single1date = October 26, 2018\n | single2     = Lightning\n | single2date = October 31, 2019\n | single3     = The Burning\n | single3date = December 13, 2019\n}}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1      = ''[[Metal Hammer]] Italia''\n| rev1score = {{Rating|6.2|10}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Schwarz |first1=Andrea |title=British Lion \u2013 The Burning |url=http://www.metalhammer.it/recensioni/2020/01/23/british-lion-the-burning/ |website=Metal Hammer Italia |accessdate=January 23, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev2      = ''Cryptic Rock''\n| rev2score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tanzi |first1=Vito |title=BRITISH LION \u2013 THE BURNING (ALBUM REVIEW) |url=https://crypticrock.com/british-lion-the-burning-album-review/ |website=Cryptic Rock |accessdate=January 15, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev3      = ''[[Classic Rock]]''\n| rev3score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lawson |first1=Dow |title=British Lion: \u2018Arry\u2019s other army return on sizzling form |url=https://www.loudersound.com/reviews/british-lion-arrys-other-army-return-on-sizzling-form |website=Louder |accessdate=January 17, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev4      = ''[[Kerrang]]''\n| rev4score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Garner |first1=George |title=ALBUM REVIEW: BRITISH LION \u2013 THE BURNING |url=https://www.kerrang.com/reviews/album-review-british-lion-the-burning/ |website=Kerrang! |accessdate=January 9, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev5      = ''Metal Temple''\n| rev5score = {{Rating|9|10}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Nowels |first1=Dave |title=British Lion \u2013 The Burning |url=http://www.metal-temple.com/site/catalogues/entry/reviews/cd_3/b_2/british-lion-the.htm |website=Metal-Temple.com |accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev6      = ''Distorted Sound''\n| rev6score = {{Rating|8|10}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Leaver |first1=Elliot |title=ALBUM REVIEW: The Burning \u2013 British Lion |url=https://distortedsoundmag.com/album-review-the-burning-british-lion/ |website=Distorted Sound Magazine |accessdate=January 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev7      = ''Planet Mosh''\n| rev7score = {{Rating|8|10}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Colson |first1=Stephen |title=The Burning \u2013 British Lion |url=https://planetmosh.com/the-burning-british-lion/ |website=PlanetMosh |accessdate=January 27, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev8      = ''Medium''\n| rev8score = {{Rating|9|10}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Maturo |first1=Dave |title=Album Review \u2014 British Lion |url=https://medium.com/@davematuro/album-review-british-lion-5604a0a929c3 |website=Medium |accessdate=January 21, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''The Burning''''' is the second album by [[Iron Maiden]]'s bass guitarist [[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]] project called [[British Lion (band)|British Lion]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Childers |first1=Chad |title=British Lion Reveal \u2018The Burning\u2019 Album Details + 2020 U.S. Tour  Read More: British Lion Reveal 'The Burning' Album Details + 2020 U.S. Tour |url=https://loudwire.com/british-lion-the-burning-album-2020-u-s-tour/?utm_source=tsmclip&utm_medium=referral |website=Loudwire |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ryan |first1=Tim |title=Local CD pick: 'The Burning,\" British Lion |url=https://eu.sctimes.com/story/entertainment/2020/01/22/local-cd-pick-the-burning-british-lion/4523344002/ |website=sctimes.com |accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Monkhouse |first1=Paul |title=Album Review : British Lion \u2013 \u2018The Burning |url=https://metalplanetmusic.com/2020/01/gig-review-british-lion-the-burning/ |website=Metal Planet Music |accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Popoff |first1=Martin |title=BRITISH LION \u2013 \u201cIT\u2019S EMOTIONAL AND IT\u2019S POWERFUL AND IT\u2019S REAL\u201d |url=http://bravewords.com/features/british-lion-its-emotional-and-its-powerful-and-its-real |website=BraveWords |accessdate=January 31, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Johnson |first1=Kevin |title=Steve Harris and British Lion Release \u201cThe Burning\u201d |url=https://www.notreble.com/buzz/2020/01/22/steve-harris-and-british-lion-release-the-burning/ |website=No Treble |accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref> It was released January 17, 2020, and was produced by Harris itself. It was the first album under only moniker British Lion, transforming the project from solo to band.\n\nThe album was preceded by the singles \"Spit Fire\" on October 26, 2018, \"Lightning\" on October 31, 2019, and the title track \"The Burning\" on December 13, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=IRON MAIDEN Bassist's BRITISH LION: Watch Music Video For 'The Burning' Title Track |url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/iron-maiden-bassists-british-lion-watch-music-video-for-the-burning-title-track/ |website=Blabbermouth.net |accessdate=January 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Kielty |first1=Martin |title=Listen to Steve Harris\u2019 New British Lion Song \u2018The Burning\u2019  Read More: Listen to Steve Harris\u2019 New British Lion Song \u2018The Burning\u2019 |url=https://ultimateclassicrock.com/british-lion-the-burning/ |website=ultimateclassicrock.com |accessdate=December 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Colothan |first1=Scott |title=Exclusive: British Lion premiere 'The Burning' video |url=https://planetradio.co.uk/planet-rock/news/rock-news/british-lion-the-burning-video/|website=planetradio.co.uk |accessdate=January 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Graff |first1=Gary |title=Steve Harris Shares Title Track to British Lion's 'The Burning': Premiere |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/8545910/british-lion-the-burning-steve-harris |website=Billboard |accessdate=November 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the release of '''''The Burning''''', critics published reviews on their thoughts of the album. '''Metal Planet Music''' voiced that \"the first thing that strikes you is the music, great hard rock with melody and class, but it\u2019s the heart and emotion that will stay with you long after the last note rings out. Coming eight years after their debut, \u2018'''''The Burning'''''\u2019 is the second album by '''British Lion''' and the [[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]] led quintet have made a record that is at once modern, nostalgic and timeless\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metalplanetmusic.com/2020/01/gig-review-british-lion-the-burning/|title=Album Review : British Lion \u2013 \u2018The Burning|last=Authoradmin|date=2020-01-22|website=Metal Planet Music|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n== Critical Reception ==\n[[Kerrang!]] mainly spoke upon the vocals of the album stating that \"the band\u2019s debut was rather a baptism of fire for singer '''Richard Taylor''', who had to weather some predictable yet redundant criticisms comparing him to [[Bruce Dickinson]] from Steve\u2019s \u201cother\u201d band. He sings like he has a point to prove throughout '''''The Burning'''''. A telling sign of the frontman\u2019s burgeoning confidence comes on '''Elysium''' \u2013 a song that boasts a killer chorus but an even better final passage, as he belts out a series of absolutely massive sustained notes over a swelling choral section. Equally impressive is his ability to extract emotion from a song. Whether he\u2019s communing with lost souls on '''Lightning''' or offering a consolatory ear on closer '''Native Son''', he often brings a moving sense of fragility to the fore. Clearly, this particular lion has more at its disposal than claws alone\"\n\n\n\n\n==Track listing==\nAll songs are written by Richard Taylor, David Hawkins and [[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]], except where noted.\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed       = \n| headline        =\n| total_length    = 60:11\n| title1          = City of Fallen Angels\n| length1         = 5:20\n| writer1         = \n\n| title2          = The Burning\n| length2         = 5:15\n| writer2         = \n\n| title3          = Father Lucifer\n| length3         = 4:38\n| writer3         = \n\n| title4          = Elysium\n| length4         = 5:11\n| writer4         =\n\n| title5          = Lightning\n| length5         = 5:49\n| writer5         = \n\n| title6          = Last Chance\n| length6         = 6:05\n| writer6         = Grahame Leslie, Ian Roberts, Taylor, Harris\n\n| title7          = Legend\n| length7         = 4:06\n| writer7         = \n\n| title8          = Spit Fire\n| length8         = 6:19\n| writer8         = \n\n| title9          = Land of the Perfect People\n| length9         = 4:52\n| writer9         = Taylor, Harris\n\n| title10         = Bible Black \n| length10        = 6:33\n| writer10        = \n\n| title11         = Native Son\n| length11        = 6:03\n| writer11        = \n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n*Richard Taylor - vocals\n*David Hawkins - guitars\n*Grahame Leslie - guitars\n*[[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]] - bass guitars, keyboards, production\n*Simon Dawson - drums\n\n===Additional personnel===\n*Tony Newton - engineering, recording, mixing\n*Ade Emsley - mastering\n*John McMurtrie - photography\n*Gustavo Sazes - album cover\n*Matt Cox - templating, booklet artwork \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Burning, The}}\n[[Category:Heavy metal albums by English artists]]\n[[Category:2020 albums]]\n", "name_user": "MichaelSharman", "label": "safe", "comment": "Citing the Kerrang! review of the burning", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Burning_(British_Lion_album)"}
{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Republic of Ireland", "text_new": "{{About|the coronavirus pandemic in the Republic of Ireland|the pandemic in Northern Ireland|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Northern Ireland}}\n{{Current event|2=current pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use Irish English|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Ireland}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Ireland\n| map1            = Confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Ireland by county.webm\n| legend1         = Confirmed cases by [[Counties of Ireland|county]]\n| alt1            = \n| map2            = Confirmed cases of COVID-19 per 100k inhabitants in Ireland.webm\n| legend2         = Confirmed cases per 100k inhabitants by [[Counties of Ireland|county]]\n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[Coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19)\n| virus_strain    = [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|Severe acute respiratory syndrome<br/>coronavirus 2]] (SARS-CoV-2)\n| source          = [[Bat]]s or possibly [[pangolin]]s<ref>{{cite journal |title=Identifying SARS-CoV-2 related coronaviruses in Malayan pangolins |journal=Nature |date=26 March 2020 |doi=10.1038/s41586-020-2169-0 |url=https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-020-2169-0_reference.pdf |accessdate=27 March 2020|last1=Lam |first1=Tommy Tsan-Yuk |last2=Shum |first2=Marcus Ho-Hin |last3=Zhu |first3=Hua-Chen |last4=Tong |first4=Yi-Gang |last5=Ni |first5=Xue-Bing |last6=Liao |first6=Yun-Shi |last7=Wei |first7=Wei |last8=Cheung |first8=William Yiu-Man |last9=Li |first9=Wen-Juan |last10=Li |first10=Lian-Feng |last11=Leung |first11=Gabriel M. |last12=Holmes |first12=Edward C. |last13=Hu |first13=Yan-Ling |last14=Guan |first14=Yi |pmid=32218527 }}</ref><ref name=\"WHO report 28 February 2020\">{{cite web |url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/who-china-joint-mission-on-covid-19-final-report.pdf |title=Report of the WHO-China Joint Mission on Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19) |date=16\u201324 February 2020 |access-date=8 March 2020 |author=WHO\u2013China Joint Mission |work=[[World Health Organization]]}}</ref><ref name=\"ia56U\">{{cite journal |title=Mystery deepens over animal source of coronavirus |journal=Nature |volume=579 |pages=18\u201319 |date=26 February 2020 |doi=10.1038/d41586-020-00548-w |pmid=32127703 |vauthors=Cyranoski D |issue=7797 |bibcode=2020Natur.579...18C|doi-access=free }}</ref>, \n| location        = [[Republic of Ireland]]\n| first_case      = [[Dublin]]\n| arrival_date    = 29 February 2020<br/>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=02|day1=29|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}} ago)\n| origin          = [[Northern Italy]] (local)<br/>[[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], [[China]] (global)<br/>{{coord|30|35|14|N|114|17|17|E|type:adm2nd_region:CN-42}}\n| recovery_cases  = 77 <small>(as of 15 April 2020)</small><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.ie/en/service/0039bc-view-the-covid-19-coronavirus-dashboard-showing-the-latest-stats-and/|title=View the COVID-19 (Coronavirus) Dashboard showing the latest stats and information|publisher=[[Department of Health (Ireland)|Department of Health]]|accessdate=9 April 2020|at=Global Stats}}</ref>{{dubious|Statistics sources - \"Recoved\" figure|date=April 2020}}\n| deaths          = 444 <small>(as of 15 April 2020)</small><ref name=\"15 April\">{{cite news|url=https://www.rte.ie/news/2020/0415/1130739-covid-ireland-update/|title=38 more people have died from Covid-19, 1,068 new cases|first=Maggie|last=Doyle|publisher=[[RT\u00c9 News and Current Affairs]]|date=15 April 2020}}</ref>\n| confirmed_cases = 12,547 <small>(as of 15 April 2020)</small><ref name=\"15 April\"/>\n| suspected_cases = \n| total_ili       = \n| website         = [https://www.gov.ie/en/news/7e0924-latest-updates-on-covid-19-coronavirus/ Gov.ie - Latest updates on COVID-19 (Coronavirus)]\n| dates           = 8 March 2020\n}}\n\nConfirmation that the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] had spread to [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]] came on 29 February 2020.<ref name=\"BBC News 1st Irish\">{{cite news |title=First case of coronavirus in Republic of Ireland |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51693259 |publisher=[[BBC News]] |date=29 February 2020 |accessdate=2020-03-02}}</ref> [[Tony Holohan]], the [[Chief Medical Officer (Ireland)|Chief Medical Officer]] for the [[Department of Health (Ireland)|Irish Department of Health]], announced its arrival.<ref name=\"BBC News 1st Irish\"/> By 20 March, around three weeks later, it was present in all [[Counties of Ireland|26 counties]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/health/coronavirus-cases-now-confirmed-in-every-county-in-ireland-1.4209389|title=Coronavirus cases now confirmed in every county in Ireland|first=Paul Cullen Health|last=Editor|website=[[The Irish Times]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejournal.ie/breakdown-county-coronavirus-ireland-5054368-Mar2020/|title=Every single county in Ireland now has at least one coronavirus case - here's a breakdown of where the virus is|first=Garreth|last=MacNamee|website=TheJournal.ie}}</ref>\n\nThe pandemic's arrival affected many aspects of society, initially including the cancellation of [[Saint Patrick's Day|St Patrick's Day]] parades and all festivals.<ref name=\"Dublin Live Pat Parade canc\"/><ref name=\"Waterford Live Pat canc\"/><ref name=\"Echo parade canc\"/><ref name=\"BBC pat parades off\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51806551|title=Irish St Patrick's Day parades off over coronavirus|date=2020-03-09|publisher=[[BBC News]] |language=en-GB |access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref> [[Taoiseach]] [[Leo Varadkar]] broke from a trip to [[Washington, D.C.]], where he was meeting with [[President of the United States]] [[Donald Trump]], to announce the closure of all schools, colleges, childcare and other public facilities until at least 29 March 2020.<ref name=\"Irish Times schools to shut\"/> These [[public health]] measures were subsequently expanded and extended until at least 19 April 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thejournal.ie/coronavirus-new-measures-5055686-Mar2020/|title=Taoiseach announces all non-essential shops to close, restrictions on gatherings of more than four people|last=Murray|first=Sean|website=[[TheJournal.ie]]|language=en|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref> Another extension carried the measures onwards until 5 May 2020 at the earliest.<ref name=\"extend\"/>\n\nOn 17 March, the [[Health Service Executive]] (HSE) launched a recruitment campaign, asking both healthcare professionals and non-healthcare professionals to \"be on call for Ireland\".<ref name=beon/> [[President of Ireland]] [[Michael D. Higgins]] signed into law [[Health (Preservation and Protection and other Emergency Measures in the Public Interest) Act 2020|an emergency bill]], which had earlier passed through the [[D\u00e1il \u00c9ireann|D\u00e1il]] and [[Seanad \u00c9ireann]], that gave the state the power to [[Detention (imprisonment)|detain]] people, restrict travel and keep people in their homes in order to help control the spread of virus.<ref name=\"RTE Higgins signs emerg\"/>\n\n<!-- Please also update the stats in the Europe page also https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Europe#Ireland -->\nAs of 15 April, the [[Department of Health (Ireland)|Department of Health]] has confirmed 12,547 cases and 444 deaths.<ref name=\"15 April\"/>\n\n== Statistics ==\nThe surveillance of COVID-19 cases has been integrated into the existing national Computerised Infectious Disease Reporting (CIDR) system since COVID-19 was made a notifiable disease on 20th February 2020. CIDR is the information system used to manage the surveillance and control of infectious diseases in Ireland, both at regional and national level.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ndsc.newsweaver.ie/4otaa688p3/c2f2qexyyf210gkzp9yxn5?a=1&p=56582761&t=31302934|title=Minister for Health signs regulations to make COVID-19 a notifiable disease in Ireland|publisher=HSE [[Health Protection Surveillance Centre]] |date=1 March 2020|accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref> Daily epidemiological reports on COVID-19 are prepared by the [[Health Protection Surveillance Centre]] for the [[National Public Health Emergency Team]] (NPHET).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.ie/en/news/7e0924-latest-updates-on-covid-19-coronavirus/|title=Latest updates on COVID-19 (Coronavirus)|publisher=[[Department of Health]] |date=10 April 2020|accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref> \n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=2\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=600\n|colors=#FF4500,#A50026,#f1f527\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-60\n|x=29 Feb,1 Mar,2 Mar,3 Mar,4 Mar,5 Mar,6 Mar,7 Mar,8 Mar,9 Mar,10 Mar,11 Mar,12 Mar,13 Mar,14 Mar,15 Mar,16 Mar,17 Mar,18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar,21 Mar,22 Mar,23 Mar,24 Mar,25 Mar,26 Mar,27 Mar,28 Mar,29 Mar, 30 Mar, 31 Mar,1 Apr,2 Apr,3 Apr,4 Apr,5 Apr,6 Apr,7 Apr,8 Apr,9 Apr,10 Apr,11 Apr,12 Apr,13 Apr,14 Apr,15 Apr\n|yAxisTitle=Cases\n|y1Title=Total confirmed cases\n|y1=1,1,1,2,6,13,18,19,21,24,34,43,70,90,129,169,223,292,366,557,683,785,906,1125,1329,1564,1819,2121,2415,2615,2910,3235,3447,3849,4273,4604,4994,5364,5709,6074,6574,8089,8928,9655,10647,11479,12547\n|y2=,,,,,,,,,,,1,1,1,2,2,2,2,2,3,3,3,4,6,7,9,19,22,36,46,54,71,85,98,120,137,158,174,210,235,263,288,320,334,365,406,444\n|y3=,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,59,84,114,147,159,208,247,283,321,375,445,506,578,674,752,841,948,1084,1163,1263,1388,1568,1765,1949,2141,2312,2489,2707,2872\n|yGrid= |xGrid=\n}}\n{{legend|#FF4500|Total confirmed cases.\n{{legend|#f1f527|Total healthcare worker confirmed cases.\n{{legend|#A50026|Total deaths.\n}}}}}}\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|width=600\n|colors=#FF4500,#000000,#87CEEB\n|type=stackedrect\n|showValues=offset\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-60\n|x=29 Feb,1 Mar,2 Mar,3 Mar,4 Mar,5 Mar,6 Mar,7 Mar,8 Mar,9 Mar,10 Mar,11 Mar,12 Mar,13 Mar,14 Mar,15 Mar,16 Mar,17 Mar,18 Mar,